Macular Degeneration: 

• Macular degeneration usually refers to the deterioration of the retina over age
• The retina is the portion of the eye, that has receptors and nerves which collect and transmit  
   the visual information to the brain

Symptoms to look for:

• Loss of vision in the centre of visual field
• Difficulty in recognising faces
• Trouble distinguishing visual features
• Straight lines look irregular or bent
• Difficulty in reading
• Images between two eyes do not sync
• Objects look different sizes in each eye

Causes:

• With age, health of eyes deteriorate
• Additional blood cells form beneath the central part of the retina

